<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Can you meet your daily needs without a car? That question opens the whole unit.</p>
  <p>The 15-minute neighbourhood is a place where daily needs (live, work, shop, learn, heal, play, move) sit within a short walk or cycle of home, so the car becomes optional rather than mandatory. Turning a neighbourhood into a 15-minute area is a land-use design problem with no win-everything answer, and Chennai (rapid growth, lost wetlands and eris, the 2015 floods, brutal heat, dense informal settlements) is a sharp test case. Unit 6 widens the lens from Unit 5's water question to the built human environment people actually live in.</p>
  <p class="sub" style="color: var(--muted);">Full block content lands in the Unit 6 deep build. This page is a navigable skeleton.</p>
</section>

